{"word":"ἀποινάω","slug":"ἀποινάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀποινάω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <a href='S:ἄποινα'><el>ἄποινα</el></a>\n<p/><i>to demand the fine</i> due from the murderer, Lex <a href='S:apud (quoted in)'>ap.</a> <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to hold to ransom</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/>"}]}